message.distributionDefaultInviterIdTip.message: The user ID of the default inviter. If the distribution link does not carry the inviter_id parameter, this user ID will be used as the inviter by default.

message.distributionForceInviterIdTip.message: The user ID of the forced inviter. If this ID is set, regardless of whether the distribution link carries the inviter_id parameter, this user ID will be forced to be used as the inviter.

message.originTip.message: Site domain name, site configuration is bound to the domain name, and the site domain name cannot be changed.

message.titleTip.message: Site title, displayed in the browser tab.

message.descriptionTip.message: Site description, located in the site metadata, used for site SEO optimization.

message.logoTip.message: Site logo, displayed at the top of the site menu when the menu bar is expanded.

message.faviconTip.message: Site favicon, displayed in the browser tab.

message.adminsTip.message: Site administrator ID. By default, the user who first creates the site will become the administrator. Only site administrators can manage the site.

message.adminsTip2.message: You can add or remove administrator IDs here. You can view user IDs at https://auth.acedata.cloud

message.keywordsTip.message: Site keywords, located in the site metadata, used for site SEO optimization.

message.keywordsTip2.message: You can add or remove site keywords here. The more precise the keywords, the more beneficial for SEO optimization.
